# Bug probe: tree.refresh does NOT re-run auto-expand for newly-added
# top-level dirs. A directory created after App::new() + tree.refresh
# remains COLLAPSED — its children are invisible until manually expanded.
#
# Real-world impact: user does `git clone repo packages/newpkg` inside
# their workspace, then `:tree.refresh` — they see `packages/newpkg`
# but NOT its children (collapsed, no expand).
#
# This test documents the current behavior so a fix is detectable.

shell mkdir -p alpha/src alpha/tests
shell echo 'export const a = 1;' > alpha/src/index.ts
shell echo 'test("a", () => {})' > alpha/tests/alpha.test.ts
shell mkdir -p beta/src
shell echo 'export const b = 2;' > beta/src/index.ts

# Refresh to pick up the new dirs
command tree.refresh

# alpha/ shows at root level (correct)
expect screen contains "alpha"
# BUT alpha/src/ is NOT visible — alpha is collapsed (not auto-expanded)
# This is the current behavior — the test documents it as a known limitation.
# If auto-expand is added to refresh, this expect should be updated to:
#   expect screen contains "src"
